lign=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wiz Lists</span><hr size=1> Ah KoL... you have the tinkering gnome leader Saphra! Always good to see that!<br>
<br>
I too have a list of those who have attempted to ruin the land of Norrath for me. I'm sure many others do to some degree or another as well. It was only about a half a year ago that I bothered to write down their offenses as well as putting them on my list. Now I can keep track of those who were either mildly annoying as well as those that truly deserved to find themselves in a &quot;bind point death loop&quot; at 4:30am.<br>
<br>
I feel a little better knowing that I'll never help those one or two complete arseholes... but oh it would be so much more grand if every Wizard they ran into snubbed them as well. In fact, why stop at Wizards. Why not include Clerics, Druids, -- heck every class!<br>
<br>
But I see two problems: How do you make sure you don't include someone who deserves to be in THE LIST from being a part of your secret society? And how do you make sure new additions to THE LIST truly deserve to be on said list?<br>
<br>
As an officer of a guild I've had ocassions where an outsider has accused a guild member of doing something so drastic that they should be deguilded. After speaking with the guild member in question, their side of the story makes it seem as if the other person was the instigator. It came down to one person's word over another. My point is that it takes an extreme amount of trust/faith or investigation to determine who was wrong.<br>
<br>
And then where do you draw the line for entry onto THE LIST? For each individual it is clear since you are your own jury. Do you put someone on a list if they lie? Do you put someone on the list if they threaten to kill steal you? What about someone who is just plain rude? At what point does the insults and foul language cross the line?<br>
<br>
As a Wizard of C-T I find the idea incredibly interesting, but the potential for abuse and wrongful additions to THE LIST seem too great to risk. Something like this would probably work well in a very small trusted group of friends, but once it grows too big you'll spend your entire day acting as judge and jury.<br>
<br>
I'd much rather see a list of people that are worthwhile to get to know better. I have a list of really good friends: I known them in RL, many hours of time spent with in Norrath, or just because of some extremely abnormal out-of-the-way acts of pure kindness.<br>
<br>
I'd much rather know who your really trusted, close, treasured, friends are. Then I can go out of my way to help them instead of going out of my way not to help some immature jerk. <p>--<br>
<font color="#770000">Mukaka Nudderbolts</font><br>
Gnomish Wizard<br>
Clockwork Tinkers Union of Cazic-Thule<br>
Master of Tinkering
