My method of keeping out the bad people<br>
--Only wizards need &quot;apply&quot; to our secret society. Gives us a brother/sisterhood feeling, we know each other from graffe and from quadding.<br>
Well..and a certain shaman who suddenly raises prices on potions to 3x the normal when facing members on the list<br>
(and gives a 10-50% discount to the people I send his way..works both ways)<br>
Yes, there is possibility for abuse on the &quot;Well...I said that he did this..I demand retribution&quot;...however, the people that I pick and choose to be within my selection of people are people I've known for months and I trust in their honour and integrity. After all, they're aggreeing to snub entire guilds from lining their own pockets.<br>
At that point, its all trust that I've done my homework on a guild or a person before rendering the decision to add to list.<br>
