<br>
But I too fear abuse of the power, as I have seen it first hand, so I dont really keep a list. I do **remember** folks that are total asses though; one of the benifits of having a near photographic memory.<br>
<br>
The people on my head list are usually such assholes that **everyone** knows about them anyway, so there is little need to spread the word.<br>
<br>
I have only had two episodes in 51 levels where I felt truly wronged by a port requester. <br>
<br>
1) Around level 30 a guy offered me some plat for an NK trip. Then berated me in /ooc for actually accepting his donation. I haven't seen him in 20 + levels though, so I assume he either got bored with that toon and rolled a new one, or quit altogether. Chances are he was too stupid to get past 35 regardless.<br>
<br>
2) Had a guy pick a fight with me in /occ because he felt all ports should be **free**, as it &quot;is only manna&quot;. I told him he was mistaken; in actuality - it is **only** time. My time, and I will charge or not charge as I see fit. BTW: I never advertise my porting services for X plat. I think its crass, and druidic to do so. Anyway - he bitched me out in /ooc for my &quot;greedy&quot; ways, and before I could reply - 3 total strangers chimed in and basically told him to go flux himself. never saw him again either...<br>
<br>
Bottom line: I port when I want to port, and I accept donations or not as I see fit. Anyone who doesn't like it can take the bus, period.<br>
<br>
Now - as to the original question: Do I keep a list of folks that I will invite, and then port exile to HATE? Of course not. That is a suspendable / banable offense on most servers (I dont know about Sullon Zek.)<br>
<br>
Which brings me to:<br>
<br>
